 Port Elizabeth - Port Elizabeth police are investigating a case where a 25-year-old security guard, who was on duty was held at gunpoint and robbed of his official firearm on Friday in Sidwell. "It is alleged that at about 17:00, complainant was parked on a road on the corners of Cadel Street and Uitenhage Road, in Sidwell," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "He was standing outside his vehicle. As he got into his vehicle, he was approached from behind by two unknown males. "As they neared the vehicle they started firing at him. The security guard fell onto the seat and the suspects leaned into the vehicle and took his 9mm pistol." Col Naidu said that it is further alleged that they got into a vehicle and sped off. "No injuries were sustained and police are investigating a case of attempted murder and armed robbery." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 